        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Learning-Two-Time-scale-Representation-for-Large-Scale-Sequential-Interaction-Data"><a href="#Learning-Two-Time-scale-Representation-for-Large-Scale-Sequential-Interaction-Data" class="headerlink" title="Learning Two Time-scale Representation for Large Scale Sequential Interaction Data"></a>Learning Two Time-scale Representation for Large Scale Sequential Interaction Data</h1><h2 id="Core-Ideas"><a href="#Core-Ideas" class="headerlink" title="Core Ideas"></a>Core Ideas</h2><h3 id="Preset"><a href="#Preset" class="headerlink" title="Preset"></a>Preset</h3><ul><li>In a dynamic network, users have interactions with items</li><li>User embedding will influence the embedding of items and the reverse also works</li></ul><h3 id="Idea"><a href="#Idea" class="headerlink" title="Idea"></a>Idea</h3><ul><li>Some active people or hot items seems static in the Graphical Network, which means that we can remove the edges linked to them</li></ul>]]></content>
      
      
      
